OL,7,FThe LGA's work is being done to mark
OL,8,F10 years since the Care Act received
OL,9,Froyal assent - which was designed to
OL,10,Fpull together a patchwork of
OL,11,Flegislation since 1948 into one single
OL,12,FAct that all councils have to comply
OL,13,Fwith.
OL,15,FUnder the legislation, councils have a
OL,16,Flegal duty- amongst others, to ensure
OL,17,Fthat their residents have access to a
OL,18,Fwide range of high-quality and
OL,19,Fappropriate services that would
OL,20,Fprevent, reduce or delay the need for
OL,21,Fcare and support.
OL,1,Wz5~k4~k7}hw1 ~k4~sj5j5~s1 G    G10/13
