OL,7,FDespite being Conservative, Fothergill
OL,8,Fargued that the promises of that
OL,9,Flegislation had not been fulfilled.
OL,11,F"The Care Act was a beacon of hope for
OL,12,Fthose needing care and support but
OL,13,Fthis hope has faded.
OL,15,F"A decade on, people are still facing
OL,16,Flong waiting times for assessments and
OL,17,Fsupport and not getting the full care
OL,18,Fand support they need."
